By virtue of the King's commission of the peace, and oyer and terminer, for the city of London, and at the general sessions of gaol delivery of Newgate, holden for the city of London and county of Middlesex at Justice-hall in the Old Baily, before the
Right Honourable Sir Thomas Chitty, Knt . Lord Mayor , the Honourable Mr. Justice Clive, one of the Judges of his Majesty's court of Common Pleas;
Sir Sidney Stafford Smythe, Knt . one of the Barons of his Majesty's court of Exchequer;
Sir William Moreton, Knt . Recorder , and others his Majesty's Justices of oyer and terminer for the said city and county; on Wednesday the 22d, Thursday the 23d, and Friday the 24th of October, in the 34th Year of his [late] Majesty's reign,
Patrick M'Carty was capitally convicted for the willful murder of
William Talbot.
